jokes.joke: Why don't programmers like nature? It has too many bugs.
What's the object-oriented way to become wealthy? Inheritance.
I would tell you a UDP joke, but you might not get it.
There are 10 types of people in the world: those who understand binary, and those who don't.
How do you comfort a JavaScript bug? You console it.
A programmer puts two glasses on his bedside table before going to sleep. A full one, in case he gets thirsty, and an empty one, in case he doesn't.
Why did the programmer quit his job? Because he didn't get arrays.
What's a programmer's favorite place to hang out? The Foo Bar.
Why do Java developers wear glasses? Because they don't C#.
I've got a great joke about networking, but I think it's over your head.
What do you call a fish with no eyes? A fsh.
Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field.
What do you get when you cross a snowman and a vampire? Frostbite.
Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything.
What do you call a lazy kangaroo? Pouch potato.
A man walks into a zoo. The only animal in the entire zoo is a dog. It's a shih tzu.
What do you call a magic dog? A Labracadabrador.
Why did the cow cross the road? To get to the udder side.
How does a penguin build its house? Igloos it together.
What did the horse say after it tripped? 'Help! I've fallen and I can't giddyup!'
My grief counselor died. He was so good, I don't even care.
I asked my date to meet me at the gym, but she never showed up. I guess the two of us aren't going to work out.
They laughed at my crayon drawing. I laughed at their chalk outline.
I told my doctor I broke my arm in two places. He told me to stop going to those places.
What's the last thing to go through a fly's mind as it hits your windshield? Its butt.
My grandfather always said 'Don't put all your eggs in one basket.' He was a terrible grocery packer.
Why don't cannibals eat clowns? Because they taste funny.
The doctor gave me one year to live, so I shot him. The judge gave me 20 years. Problem solved.
It's important to have a good vocabulary. If I had known the difference between 'antidote' and 'anecdote,' one of my best friends would still be alive.
You don't need a parachute to go skydiving. You need a parachute to go skydiving twice.
I was sober for a year but it was the worst year of my life.
A dyslexic man walks into a bra.
I'm on a whiskey diet. I've lost three days already.
Reality is an illusion that occurs due to a lack of alcohol.
An Irishman walks out of a bar. It could happen!
Why did the man get fired from the brewery? He was caught drinking on the job.
I saw a sign that said 'Drink Canada Dry.' So I did.
I don't have a drinking problem. I drink, I get drunk, I fall down. No problem.
What's the difference between a drunk and a potty? One is a vessel for waste, and the other is a toilet.
My doctor told me to watch my drinking. So I'm off to a bar with a view.
Why was the motherboard so sad? Her kids wouldn't chip in for her birthday.
I have a joke about a computer's memory, but I forgot it.
What's a computer's favorite snack? Microchips.
What does a computer do for lunch? It has a byte.
What do you call a computer that sings? A-dell.
Why was the computer cold? It left its Windows open.
What's the best way to learn about computers? From a book, because they have a hard drive.
Why did the computer get a promotion? It had a lot of drive.
What do you call a computer floating in the ocean? A Dell rolling in the deep.
Why did the computer go to the doctor? It had a bad case of the blue screen of death.
What did the spider do on the computer? It made a website.
Why did the computer get a divorce? It couldn't find its space bar.
What do you call a computer that's always hungry? A cookie monster.
Why did the computer get a ticket? It was speeding on the information superhighway.
What's a computer's favorite beat? An algo-rhythm.
What do you call a computer that's always late? A lag-top.
Why was the CPU so good at music? Because it had a lot of cores.
What did the motherboard say to the CPU? 'You're the brains of this operation.'
Why did the GPU go to art school? To work on its rendering.
Why do programmers prefer dark mode? Because light attracts bugs.
A programmer is at work when his wife calls. She says, 'Please go to the store. Buy a gallon of milk, and if they have eggs, buy a dozen.' He comes home with 12 gallons of milk.
My grandfather said my generation relies too much on technology. So I unplugged his life support.
How many programmers does it take to change a light bulb? None. That's a hardware problem.
What's the difference between a Lamborghini and a dead body? I don't have a Lamborghini in my garage.
I just read that someone in New York gets stabbed every 52 seconds. Poor guy.
Why do programmers always mix up Halloween and Christmas? Because Oct 31 equals Dec 25.
Debugging is like being the detective in a crime movie where you are also the murderer.
Why was the developer broke? Because he used up all his cache.
My code works. I have no idea why. My code doesn't work. I have no idea why.
A SQL query goes into a bar, walks up to two tables and asks, 'Can I join you?'
I told my wife she should embrace her mistakes. She gave me a hug.
Programming is like sex: one mistake and you have to support it for the rest of your life.
Why was the JavaScript developer sad? Because he didn't Node how to Express himself.
An apple a day keeps the doctor away. Or at least it does if you throw it hard enough.
To understand recursion, you must first understand recursion.
I have a joke about trickle-down economics. But 99% of you will never get it.
I have an inferiority complex, but it's not a very good one.
I let my kids vote on dinner. They picked tacos. I made pizza. They don't live in a swing state.
What is the most used language in programming? Profanity.
My wife is leaving me because of my obsession with pasta. I'm feeling cannelloni right now.
I started a band called 1023 Megabytes. We haven't gotten a gig yet.
Why can't orphans play baseball? They don't know where home is.
A good programmer is someone who always looks both ways before crossing a one-way street.
I'd like to make a joke about the cloud, but it would just go over your head.
My password is 'incorrect'. So every time I forget it, my computer tells me 'Your password is incorrect.'
My wife told me I'm a real paradox. So I pushed her down the stairs.
The best thing about a boolean is even if you are wrong, you are only off by a bit.
What's the difference between a frontend and a backend developer? A frontend developer has to make things pretty.
My computer says 'Press any key to continue'. Where is the 'Any' key?
My therapist said my narcissism is causing me to misread social cues. I'm pretty sure she was hitting on me.
How do you generate a random string? Put a Windows user in front of Vim and tell them to exit.
Why don't vampires like making websites? They're afraid of the cascade.
My girlfriend's dog died, so I tried to cheer her up by getting her an identical one. It just made her more upset. She was crying, 'What am I going to do with two dead dogs?'
I have a lot of growing up to do. I realized that the other day inside my fort.
The box said 'Requires Windows 10 or better'. So I installed Linux.
There are only two hard things in Computer Science: cache invalidation, naming things, and off-by-one errors.
My dad died when we couldn't remember his blood type. As he passed, he kept insisting for us to 'be positive,' but it's hard without him.
